#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.157"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.157:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.157:0.2"
msgid "16. Saddhammavagga "
msgstr "16. The True Teaching "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.157:0.3"
msgid "157. Dukkathāsutta "
msgstr "157. Inappropriate Talk "

# NOTE: This is a difficult idiom to get right. I follow the Comm. reading of “puggalam puggalam”. BB has “weigh one type of person against the other”. Upanidhaya normally has the meaning of “compare”, but I am not sure how that makes sense here. You’re not comparing people, you’re assessing what is approppriate for this specific person. Comm. says “taṃ taṃ puggalaṃ upanikkhipitvā, sakkhiṃ katvā”, which (I think!) implies specificity rather than distribution, i.e. “examining that specific person”. As for the rest, I have translated according to the sense as best I can. The meaning is clear enough from what follows.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.181, sc1
#. VAR: puggale puggalaṃ → puggalaṃ puggalaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.157:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcannaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalānaṃ kathā dukkathā puggale puggalaṃ upanidhāya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are certain topics that are inappropriate to talk about, taking into consideration which specific one of five people you are talking to. "

msgctxt "an5.157:1.2"
msgid "Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.157:1.3"
msgid "Assaddhassa, bhikkhave, saddhākathā dukkathā; "
msgstr "It’s inappropriate to talk to an unfaithful person about faith. "

msgctxt "an5.157:1.4"
msgid "dussīlassa sīlakathā dukkathā; "
msgstr "It’s inappropriate to talk to an unethical person about ethics. "

msgctxt "an5.157:1.5"
msgid "appassutassa bāhusaccakathā dukkathā; "
msgstr "It’s inappropriate to talk to an unlearned person about learning. "

#. VAR: maccharissa → macchariyassa (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an5.157:1.6"
msgid "maccharissa cāgakathā dukkathā; "
msgstr "It’s inappropriate to talk to a stingy person about generosity. "

msgctxt "an5.157:1.7"
msgid "duppaññassa paññākathā dukkathā. "
msgstr "It’s inappropriate to talk to a witless person about wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.157:2.1"
msgid "Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, assaddhassa saddhākathā dukkathā? "
msgstr "And why is it inappropriate to talk to an unfaithful person about faith? "

msgctxt "an5.157:2.2"
msgid "Assaddho, bhikkhave, saddhākathāya kacchamānāya abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti. "
msgstr "When an unfaithful person is spoken to about faith they lose their temper, becoming annoyed, hostile, and hard-hearted, and displaying annoyance, hate, and bitterness. "

msgctxt "an5.157:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

#. VAR: na samanupassati → na sampassati (bj)
msgctxt "an5.157:2.4"
msgid "Tañhi so, bhikkhave, saddhāsampadaṃ attani na samanupassati, na ca labhati tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ. "
msgstr "Not seeing that faith in themselves, they don’t get the rapture and joy that faith brings. "

msgctxt "an5.157:2.5"
msgid "Tasmā assaddhassa saddhākathā dukkathā. "
msgstr "That’s why it’s inappropriate to talk to an unfaithful person about faith. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.157:3.1"
msgid "Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, dussīlassa sīlakathā dukkathā? "
msgstr "And why is it inappropriate to talk to an unethical person about ethics? "

msgctxt "an5.157:3.2"
msgid "Dussīlo, bhikkhave, sīlakathāya kacchamānāya abhisajjati kuppati byāpajjati patitthīyati kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti. "
msgstr "When an unethical person is spoken to about ethics they lose their temper … "

msgctxt "an5.157:3.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an5.157:3.4"
msgid "Tañhi so, bhikkhave, sīlasampadaṃ attani na samanupassati na ca labhati tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ. "
msgstr "Not seeing that ethical conduct in themselves, they don’t get the rapture and joy that ethical conduct brings. "

msgctxt "an5.157:3.5"
msgid "Tasmā dussīlassa sīlakathā dukkathā. "
msgstr "That’s why it’s inappropriate to talk to an unethical person about ethics. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
