msgctxt "an5.157:6.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an5.157:6.4"
msgid "Tañhi so, bhikkhave, paññāsampadaṃ attani na samanupassati, na ca labhati tatonidānaṃ pītipāmojjaṃ. "
msgstr "Not seeing that wisdom in themselves, they don’t get the rapture and joy that wisdom brings. "

msgctxt "an5.157:6.5"
msgid "Tasmā duppaññassa paññākathā dukkathā. "
msgstr "That’s why it’s inappropriate to talk to a witless person about wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.157:6.6"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ puggalānaṃ kathā dukkathā puggale puggalaṃ upanidhāya. "
msgstr "These are topics that are inappropriate to talk about, taking into consideration which specific one of five people you are talking to. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an5.157:7.1"
msgid "Pañcannaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalānaṃ kathā sukathā puggale puggalaṃ upanidhāya. "
msgstr "There are certain topics that are appropriate to talk about, taking into consideration which specific one of five people you are talking to. "

msgctxt "an5.157:7.2"
msgid "Katamesaṃ pañcannaṃ? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.157:7.3"
msgid "Saddhassa, bhikkhave, saddhākathā sukathā; "
msgstr "It’s appropriate to talk to a faithful person about faith. "

msgctxt "an5.157:7.4"
msgid "sīlavato sīlakathā sukathā; "
msgstr "It’s appropriate to talk to an ethical person about ethical conduct. "

msgctxt "an5.157:7.5"
msgid "bahussutassa bāhusaccakathā sukathā; "
msgstr "It’s appropriate to talk to a learned person about learning. "

msgctxt "an5.157:7.6"
msgid "cāgavato cāgakathā sukathā; "
msgstr "It’s appropriate to talk to a generous person about generosity. "

msgctxt "an5.157:7.7"
msgid "paññavato paññākathā sukathā. "
msgstr "It’s appropriate to talk to a wise person about wisdom. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an5.157:8.1"
msgid "Kasmā ca, bhikkhave, saddhassa saddhākathā sukathā? "
msgstr "And why is it appropriate to talk to a faithful person about faith? "

msgctxt "an5.157:8.2"
msgid "Saddho, bhikkhave, saddhākathāya kacchamānāya nābhisajjati na kuppati na byāpajjati na patitthīyati na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti. "
msgstr "When a faithful person is spoken to about faith they don’t lose their temper, they don’t get annoyed, hostile, and hard-hearted, or display annoyance, hate, and bitterness. "

